4
5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE ADMINISTRATION OF
6 PROPERTY EXEMPTIONS; REQUIRING THE DEPARTMENT OF REVENUE TO ESTABLISH A REVIEW
7 PROCESS FOR EXEMPT PROPERTY; REQUIRING THE DEPARTMENT OF REVENUE TO MAINTAIN
8 PUBLIC INFORMATION ABOUT EXEMPT PROPERTY; ESTABLISHING REPORTING REQUIREMENTS;
9 AND PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Periodic review of exempt property -- rulemaking. (1) The department
14 shall administer a program for the review of property that is exempt from taxation under Title 15, chapter 6, part
15 2, as provided in this section.
16 (2) The review process must provide for the review of all exempt property for which an application
17 to the department is required at least once every 8 years.
18 (3) The department shall report to the revenue interim committee biennially in accordance with 5-
19 11-210 information on exempt property reviewed during the biennium, including:
20 (a) the number of properties reviewed;
21 (b) the types of exemptions reviewed;
22 (c) the number of exemptions granted and denied; and
23 (d) the estimated market value and taxable value of exemptions granted and denied.
24 (4) The department may adopt rules to implement the exempt property review process provided for
25 in this section.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Public information on exempt property. (1) The department shall
28 maintain public information about real property that is exempt from property taxation under Title 15, chapter 6,
